1
00:00:10,500 --> 00:00:12,533
<i>Bobby, Bobby, listen carefully.</i>

2
00:00:12,667 --> 00:00:16,633
<i>Glen killed the seller
of pimple patches.</i>

3
00:00:16,767 --> 00:00:18,200
<i> He's the mastermind.</i>

4
00:00:18,333 --> 00:00:19,500
<i> You made me this way!</i>

5
00:00:19,633 --> 00:00:20,500
<i> Because of you!</i>

6
00:00:20,633 --> 00:00:23,167
<i>I don't have a son
who kills people!</i>

7
00:00:23,300 --> 00:00:24,733
<i> You really don't know</i>

8
00:00:24,867 --> 00:00:27,000
<i>all the things I've done
for you!</i>

9
00:00:27,133 --> 00:00:28,833
<i> You should be thanking me!</i>

10
00:00:28,967 --> 00:00:31,233
<i>I don't have a son
who's a demon!</i>

11
00:00:31,367 --> 00:00:32,800
<i> You're an animal!</i>

12
00:00:32,933 --> 00:00:34,567
<i> Dad, you need to drink this.</i>

13
00:00:34,733 --> 00:00:36,633
<i>- Take it.
- Give that...</i>

14
00:00:36,767 --> 00:00:39,000
<i> Crawl.</i>

15
00:00:39,133 --> 00:00:40,867
<i>- Goodbye, Dad.
- Hidalgo Street?</i>

16
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:42,433
<i>- That's right near here.
- Bobby?</i>

17
00:00:42,567 --> 00:00:44,100
<i>They've been looking for you
at the party for some time now.</i>

18
00:00:44,233 --> 00:00:45,133
<i> Something happened to daddy.</i>

19
00:00:45,267 --> 00:00:47,200
<i>Let's take him
to the hospital, quick!</i>

20
00:00:47,333 --> 00:00:48,600
<i> Father...</i>

21
00:00:48,733 --> 00:00:50,767
<i> Fight, Father!</i>

22
00:00:50,900 --> 00:00:52,300
<i> Glen, what happened?</i>

23
00:00:52,433 --> 00:00:54,533
<i>We were just talking,
then he suddenly had an attack.</i>

24
00:00:54,667 --> 00:00:56,333
<i> What are you doing here?</i>

25
00:00:56,467 --> 00:00:59,133
<i>You're not part of the family,
go away!</i>

26
00:00:59,267 --> 00:01:00,233
<i> What are you doing here?</i>

27
00:01:00,367 --> 00:01:01,733
<i>Boss, the Mayor was rushed
to the hospital.</i>

28
00:01:01,867 --> 00:01:02,900
<i> Why? What happened?</i>

29
00:01:03,033 --> 00:01:04,567
<i> I heard he had a stroke.</i>

30
00:01:07,100 --> 00:01:09,467
<i> Tonyo, it's father...</i>

31
00:01:20,133 --> 00:01:22,700
Glen, what happened?

32
00:01:22,833 --> 00:01:25,000
You need to fix this, Cecilia.

33
00:01:25,133 --> 00:01:26,600
What do you mean?

34
00:01:33,733 --> 00:01:36,333
My dad saw me
kill someone earlier.

35
00:01:36,467 --> 00:01:38,033
What?

36
00:01:40,467 --> 00:01:42,833
That's probably
why he was stressed,

37
00:01:42,967 --> 00:01:46,333
then he suddenly had an attack.

38
00:01:49,033 --> 00:01:52,033
But I have,
I have a plan.

39
00:01:52,167 --> 00:01:54,300
Listen, Cecilia.

40
00:01:55,233 --> 00:01:57,100
If the doctors can revive him,

41
00:01:57,233 --> 00:01:59,400
Cecilia, listen to me.

42
00:01:59,533 --> 00:02:02,033
I need you to do
something for me.

43
00:02:02,167 --> 00:02:04,867
Are you seriously
asking me this?

44
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:07,667
We're talking about your father.

45
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:10,267
Wait a minute,
why do you suddenly

46
00:02:10,400 --> 00:02:12,267
have a conscience?

47
00:02:12,400 --> 00:02:13,733
I was fine destroying

48
00:02:13,900 --> 00:02:16,233
Victor Santiago's reputation
for you,

49
00:02:16,367 --> 00:02:17,967
but this...

50
00:02:18,100 --> 00:02:20,867
Cecilia, you don't understand.

51
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:24,800
If my dad lives, I'm dead.

52
00:02:24,933 --> 00:02:27,333
So please do this for me.

53
00:02:27,467 --> 00:02:29,133
Please.

54
00:02:31,600 --> 00:02:33,767
Cecilia...

55
00:02:33,900 --> 00:02:35,833
Cecilia!

56
00:02:45,300 --> 00:02:47,000
Tonyo, it's father.

57
00:03:02,933 --> 00:03:04,800
What's the update, Doc?

58
00:03:04,933 --> 00:03:06,467
I'm sorry.

59
00:03:06,600 --> 00:03:08,367
We did everything.

60
00:03:13,100 --> 00:03:14,400
The Mayor is dead.

61
00:03:14,533 --> 00:03:16,533
What?
No, no!

62
00:03:16,667 --> 00:03:19,233
No, Doc!
Not yet, no, no!

63
00:03:19,367 --> 00:03:21,500
Not yet, Doc!

64
00:03:21,667 --> 00:03:22,833
Doc, no.

65
00:03:22,967 --> 00:03:24,833
Mom?

66
00:03:24,967 --> 00:03:26,033
No, Doc!

67
00:03:28,400 --> 00:03:31,700
Your daddy!

68
00:03:31,833 --> 00:03:33,867
It's not true!

69
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:35,000
Dad!

70
00:03:35,133 --> 00:03:37,733
Daddy!

71
00:03:37,867 --> 00:03:39,400
It's going be okay,
it's going be okay,

72
00:03:39,533 --> 00:03:42,167
it's going be okay.

73
00:03:42,300 --> 00:03:44,033
No!

74
00:03:47,667 --> 00:03:50,433
Why? What happened?

75
00:03:50,567 --> 00:03:53,967
It's not true! Your daddy!

76
00:03:54,100 --> 00:03:57,733
No!

77
00:03:57,900 --> 00:04:00,733
Joaquin!

78
00:04:38,167 --> 00:04:40,133
Mommy ...

79
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:53,600
Daddy...

80
00:05:02,600 --> 00:05:04,300
Daddy...

81
00:05:05,400 --> 00:05:07,400
- Joaquin...
- Daddy...

82
00:05:08,733 --> 00:05:11,400
Joaquin!

83
00:05:11,533 --> 00:05:13,200
Daddy!

84
00:05:15,400 --> 00:05:18,733
Joaquin, don't, I can't.

85
00:05:18,867 --> 00:05:21,467
<i> Joaquin, how are you feeling?</i>

86
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:25,667
<i> I'm okay, Sophia.</i>

87
00:05:25,800 --> 00:05:29,667
<i>I'm just grateful
that I'm still alive.</i>

88
00:05:31,200 --> 00:05:32,600
<i> I'm sorry.</i>

89
00:05:32,733 --> 00:05:35,567
<i> I should have listened to you.</i>

90
00:05:38,667 --> 00:05:41,533
Oh, don't go, Joaquin!

91
00:05:46,367 --> 00:05:49,467
<i>Didn't I promise to help you
with the campaign?</i>

92
00:05:49,600 --> 00:05:51,467
<i> So what can I be of service?</i>

93
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:52,700
<i> Hi!</i>

94
00:05:52,833 --> 00:05:55,833
<i>Hi! See you in the upcoming
elections!</i>

95
00:06:03,633 --> 00:06:06,433
No, Joaquin!

96
00:06:08,500 --> 00:06:09,767
<i> Thank you, Glen.</i>

97
00:06:09,900 --> 00:06:11,400
<i> I'm proud of you.</i>

98
00:06:11,533 --> 00:06:14,867
<i>You are my partner
in taking care of Calabari.</i>

99
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:17,333
<i> I got to hand it to you, Son.</i>

100
00:06:17,467 --> 00:06:19,833
<i>You're already learning
the ropes.</i>

101
00:06:19,967 --> 00:06:24,733
<i>For sure, you have a good
impression with the press.</i>

102
00:06:44,167 --> 00:06:45,600
Go ahead.

103
00:06:46,900 --> 00:06:49,267
Your father is waiting for you.

104
00:07:21,600 --> 00:07:23,733
<i> Father...</i>

105
00:07:23,867 --> 00:07:25,733
<i> Father?</i>

106
00:07:25,867 --> 00:07:28,467
<i> Is what I heard true?</i>

107
00:07:28,600 --> 00:07:30,100
<i> You called me "Father"?</i>

108
00:07:30,233 --> 00:07:31,733
<i> From now on,</i>

109
00:07:31,867 --> 00:07:35,033
<i> I accept that I have a father.</i>

110
00:07:37,333 --> 00:07:39,367
<i> Thank you very much, my child.</i>

111
00:07:46,600 --> 00:07:49,700
What are you doing here?

112
00:07:49,867 --> 00:07:53,800
Can't you just let our family
grieve?

113
00:07:54,967 --> 00:07:56,800
Get out! Get out!

114
00:07:56,933 --> 00:07:58,500
Get out of here!

115
00:07:58,633 --> 00:08:01,567
Get out!
You're not our family!

116
00:08:09,933 --> 00:08:12,000
Joaquin...

117
00:08:29,567 --> 00:08:33,067
<i>I think Bobby knows where he is.</i>

118
00:08:33,200 --> 00:08:34,633
<i> Bobby? Why Bobby?</i>

119
00:08:34,767 --> 00:08:37,000
<i> Well, earlier, I heard Bobby</i>

120
00:08:37,133 --> 00:08:39,400
<i>talking to the Mayor
on the phone.</i>

121
00:08:39,533 --> 00:08:42,100
<i>Then look now,
she's not here, right?</i>

122
00:08:42,233 --> 00:08:43,667
<i> She left.</i>

123
00:08:53,167 --> 00:08:55,967
What was the last thing
you and my husband talked about?

124
00:08:56,133 --> 00:08:58,200
- Ma'am...
- And why didn't you tell anyone

125
00:08:58,333 --> 00:09:00,100
you were going to see him?

126
00:09:00,233 --> 00:09:02,633
Ma'am, I don't know,
he just called me.

127
00:09:02,767 --> 00:09:03,667
When I got there,

128
00:09:03,800 --> 00:09:04,933
he and Glen were together.

129
00:09:05,067 --> 00:09:07,167
Why are you involving Glen here?

130
00:09:07,300 --> 00:09:09,467
You know, honestly,
just go away!

131
00:09:09,600 --> 00:09:10,933
I don't want to see you here!

132
00:09:11,067 --> 00:09:13,267
Don't come near us!
You're unlucky!

133
00:09:13,400 --> 00:09:15,167
Ma'am, please excuse me!

134
00:09:16,133 --> 00:09:18,700
I know you're all hurting
because of the Mayor's loss,

135
00:09:18,833 --> 00:09:20,600
but let's not blame others.

136
00:09:20,733 --> 00:09:22,267
It's not Bobby's fault here.

137
00:09:22,400 --> 00:09:23,900
You know, you too!

138
00:09:24,033 --> 00:09:25,500
You two leave here!

139
00:09:25,633 --> 00:09:27,000
We don't want to see you!

140
00:09:27,133 --> 00:09:30,033
You're the jinx in our lives!

141
00:09:30,200 --> 00:09:31,667
Go away!

142
00:09:31,800 --> 00:09:33,833
Mom, Mom, that's enough,
that's enough, please.

143
00:09:33,967 --> 00:09:35,367
Go away!

144
00:09:35,500 --> 00:09:36,733
Don't show yourself to us!

145
00:09:36,867 --> 00:09:38,633
You're not part of our family!

146
00:09:41,667 --> 00:09:43,267
You're such a thick-faced!

147
00:09:47,100 --> 00:09:49,933
What? Are you going
to piss me off again?

148
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:52,400
Have you heard?

149
00:09:52,833 --> 00:09:53,933
What's that again?

150
00:09:54,433 --> 00:09:56,367
The Mayor is dead.

151
00:09:56,500 --> 00:09:57,500
What?

152
00:09:57,633 --> 00:10:00,100
What a shame,
he's my idol.

153
00:10:00,233 --> 00:10:01,567
Oh my...

154
00:10:01,733 --> 00:10:04,033
Oh my, he's my idol too.

155
00:10:05,833 --> 00:10:08,200
That's terrible, isn't it?
It's shocking.

156
00:10:08,333 --> 00:10:09,833
What happened?

157
00:10:11,033 --> 00:10:13,367
I think he had a stroke,
it seems like that.

158
00:10:19,200 --> 00:10:20,967
Cecilia, how are you?

159
00:10:22,267 --> 00:10:24,467
Oh, what's the news
about the Mayor?

160
00:10:27,800 --> 00:10:30,900
Eric, let's just catch up
next time, okay?

161
00:10:32,467 --> 00:10:33,933
Oh, okay.

162
00:10:41,933 --> 00:10:45,167
<i>We received
some sad news tonight.</i>

163
00:10:45,300 --> 00:10:47,500
<i> Our beloved mayor,</i>

164
00:10:47,633 --> 00:10:49,467
<i> Joaquin "El Hepe" Guerrero,</i>

165
00:10:49,600 --> 00:10:51,200
<i>has passed away after being
rushed to the hospital</i>

166
00:10:51,333 --> 00:10:52,700
<i> due to a severe stroke</i>

167
00:10:52,833 --> 00:10:55,400
<i>that resulted
in a brain hemorrhage.</i>

168
00:10:55,533 --> 00:10:56,900
<i> According to the doctors,</i>

169
00:10:57,033 --> 00:11:00,067
<i>he arrived at the hospital
with a weak pulse,</i>

170
00:11:00,200 --> 00:11:03,667
<i>but his condition
did not improve.</i>

171
00:11:03,800 --> 00:11:05,033
<i> He was declared dead,</i>

172
00:11:05,167 --> 00:11:07,633
<i>at around nine twenty-four
in the evening.</i>

173
00:11:07,800 --> 00:11:10,667
<i>Mayor Joaquin was known
as a seasoned actor</i>

174
00:11:10,800 --> 00:11:13,400
<i> before he entered politics.</i>

175
00:11:13,533 --> 00:11:14,567
<i> As a politician,</i>

176
00:11:14,700 --> 00:11:17,133
<i>he is known
for suppressing criminality</i>

177
00:11:17,267 --> 00:11:19,167
throughout Calabari.

178
00:11:19,300 --> 00:11:21,933
For now, the city is expressing
its condolences

179
00:11:22,067 --> 00:11:23,867
to the Guerrero family.

180
00:11:24,000 --> 00:11:28,067
His friends and town folks
are expected to flock

181
00:11:28,200 --> 00:11:30,367
to the funeral
that will be held.

182
00:11:31,400 --> 00:11:33,633
Have you called Bobby yet?

183
00:11:33,767 --> 00:11:36,867
Cap, we can't contact her.

184
00:11:37,000 --> 00:11:38,067
Me too, Cap.

185
00:11:38,200 --> 00:11:41,500
I've been trying to call her,
but she's not answering.

186
00:11:41,667 --> 00:11:44,533
This must be very painful
for Bobby,

187
00:11:44,667 --> 00:11:46,167
for my grandchild.

188
00:11:48,767 --> 00:11:50,633
Stop crying, Captain.

189
00:11:52,600 --> 00:11:54,233
<i> Today, is set to be taken</i>

190
00:11:54,367 --> 00:11:55,733
<i> to his final resting place,</i>

191
00:11:55,867 --> 00:11:57,633
the beloved mayor of Calabari,

192
00:11:57,767 --> 00:12:00,200
Mayor Joaquin "El Hepe"
Guerrero.

193
00:12:00,333 --> 00:12:02,433
<i>All of the Mayor's fellow
citizens are mourning</i>

194
00:12:02,567 --> 00:12:04,800
<i> because of his sudden passing.</i>

195
00:12:04,933 --> 00:12:07,267
It is remembered
that El Hepe just won

196
00:12:07,400 --> 00:12:12,467
<i>the last election with his son,
Vice Mayor Glen Guerrero,</i>

197
00:12:12,600 --> 00:12:14,367
<i> who is expected to replace him</i>

198
00:12:14,500 --> 00:12:17,133
<i> as the new mayor of Calabari.</i>

199
00:12:17,300 --> 00:12:21,433
Bobby, are you sure
you really want to drink?

200
00:12:21,567 --> 00:12:23,200
You don't really drink.

201
00:12:23,333 --> 00:12:25,100
Do you regret...

202
00:12:25,233 --> 00:12:27,533
not going to your father's
funeral earlier?

203
00:12:28,567 --> 00:12:30,833
I don't want to cause trouble.

204
00:12:30,967 --> 00:12:34,900
You know Ma'am Sophia
is mad at me, right?

205
00:12:35,033 --> 00:12:36,867
I'll just pray for father.

206
00:12:37,000 --> 00:12:40,333
You know, Bobby,
I find it weird.

207
00:12:40,467 --> 00:12:41,533
Why?

208
00:12:41,667 --> 00:12:45,400
Why are the Mayor and Vice Mayor
together in that place?

209
00:12:45,533 --> 00:12:48,133
We know it's secluded.

210
00:12:48,300 --> 00:12:50,000
What do you care, Abdul?

211
00:12:50,133 --> 00:12:51,667
Bobby said it,

212
00:12:51,800 --> 00:12:54,400
the father and son
had a heart-to-heart talk.

213
00:12:54,533 --> 00:12:56,900
Heart-to-heart, and then
he suddenly had a stroke.

214
00:12:57,033 --> 00:12:59,000
- What was that, right?
- Right?

215
00:13:00,067 --> 00:13:01,233
What now, girl?

216
00:13:01,367 --> 00:13:02,633
Are you still going to visit
your siblings

217
00:13:02,767 --> 00:13:04,200
with Mayor Joaquin?

218
00:13:04,333 --> 00:13:05,600
Not anymore.

219
00:13:05,733 --> 00:13:09,233
You know, the mother of
my siblings is allergic to me.

220
00:13:09,367 --> 00:13:11,900
What about the youngest girl?

221
00:13:12,033 --> 00:13:13,933
Aren't you close to her?

222
00:13:14,067 --> 00:13:17,533
And she treat you like a sister.

223
00:13:21,667 --> 00:13:23,200
Bobby.

224
00:13:25,033 --> 00:13:26,767
Oh, Sir Tonyo, you're here.

225
00:13:26,900 --> 00:13:28,400
Move over.

226
00:13:30,233 --> 00:13:31,833
Thank you.

227
00:13:36,833 --> 00:13:38,433
How are you?

228
00:13:42,200 --> 00:13:43,833
I'm okay.

229
00:13:43,967 --> 00:13:46,433
I just don't want to be alone.

230
00:13:46,567 --> 00:13:48,767
But tomorrow, I'm going to work.

231
00:13:49,633 --> 00:13:51,233
You're going to work right away?

232
00:13:51,367 --> 00:13:52,533
Bobby, you need to rest.

233
00:13:52,667 --> 00:13:55,933
Believe me,
I've been through that.

234
00:13:56,100 --> 00:13:57,767
I know that.

235
00:13:57,900 --> 00:14:01,533
I've been through that too,
haven't I with godmother.

236
00:14:02,500 --> 00:14:03,833
So I know the feeling too.

237
00:14:03,967 --> 00:14:06,567
T hat break doesn't affect me.

238
00:14:10,733 --> 00:14:12,267
Sorry.

239
00:14:16,333 --> 00:14:17,867
I'm sorry too.

240
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:22,167
Well, if you need someone
to talk to,

241
00:14:22,300 --> 00:14:24,567
just call me anytime.

242
00:14:40,500 --> 00:14:43,133
<i> It's mine, I need it.</i>

243
00:14:47,600 --> 00:14:49,533
<i> Sorry, Dad.</i>

244
00:14:49,667 --> 00:14:51,767
<i> You shouldn't have died...</i>

245
00:14:51,900 --> 00:14:54,167
<i> but it's your fault too.</i>

246
00:14:55,967 --> 00:14:58,567
<i> I wish you hadn't bothered.</i>

247
00:14:59,800 --> 00:15:02,300
<i>I wish you'd just kept
your mouth shut</i>

248
00:15:02,467 --> 00:15:05,300
<i> if you knew anything about me.</i>

249
00:15:11,233 --> 00:15:13,033
<i> I'm not a bad kid,</i>

250
00:15:14,467 --> 00:15:16,467
<i> but I won't let you</i>

251
00:15:16,600 --> 00:15:19,967
<i> ruin all my dreams either.</i>

252
00:15:28,200 --> 00:15:30,800
<i>I'll apologize to you
next time...</i>

253
00:15:31,867 --> 00:15:35,333
<i> when we meet in hell.</i>

254
00:15:40,600 --> 00:15:42,433
Sergeant Enriquez?

255
00:15:43,500 --> 00:15:46,200
Your grandmother said
you were here.

256
00:15:46,333 --> 00:15:48,400
By the way,

257
00:15:48,533 --> 00:15:50,833
I'm Attorney Noel Cariaga,

258
00:15:50,967 --> 00:15:52,467
the Mayor's family attorney.

259
00:15:52,600 --> 00:15:54,833
Oh, Attorney, what do you need?

260
00:15:54,967 --> 00:15:59,033
I would like to invite you
to our office.

261
00:16:10,200 --> 00:16:12,900
Attorney, we can start now.

262
00:16:13,033 --> 00:16:16,700
Ma'am, can we wait a moment?

263
00:16:16,833 --> 00:16:18,200
We're still waiting for someone.

264
00:16:19,500 --> 00:16:20,833
Who?

265
00:16:26,100 --> 00:16:27,767
Sergeant Enriquez.

266
00:16:28,867 --> 00:16:30,500
Oh, sit down, sit down.

267
00:16:32,800 --> 00:16:34,667
Oh, here.

268
00:16:36,100 --> 00:16:39,033
Attorney, what's that woman
doing here?

269
00:16:39,167 --> 00:16:41,333
Sergeant Enriquez is here

270
00:16:41,500 --> 00:16:45,033
because she's one
of Mayor Joaquin's inheritors.

271
00:16:45,167 --> 00:16:46,833
What?

272
00:16:46,967 --> 00:16:47,833
That's absurd!

273
00:16:47,967 --> 00:16:49,000
- Are you kidding me?
- Mom, mom.

274
00:16:49,133 --> 00:16:51,900
Please sit down,
calm down, please.

275
00:16:52,033 --> 00:16:53,667
That's enough.

276
00:16:55,033 --> 00:16:56,133
Okay...

277
00:16:56,267 --> 00:16:59,400
I just want to know what kind
of nonsense this is.

278
00:16:59,533 --> 00:17:01,067
What was bequeathed to her?

279
00:17:01,200 --> 00:17:03,867
I want proof.

280
00:17:04,000 --> 00:17:06,567
Here are the documents,
Ma'am Sophia.

281
00:17:06,700 --> 00:17:08,667
Here's your copy.

282
00:17:10,267 --> 00:17:11,933
<i> This is your copy.</i>

283
00:17:12,067 --> 00:17:13,667
<i> There.</i>

284
00:17:15,567 --> 00:17:16,933
As you can see,

285
00:17:17,067 --> 00:17:19,867
most of the properties
and assets

286
00:17:20,000 --> 00:17:23,567
were equally divided
among the three of you.

287
00:17:23,700 --> 00:17:27,633
And the only thing left
to bequeath to Miss Enriquez

288
00:17:27,767 --> 00:17:29,800
is the rest house in Batangas

289
00:17:29,933 --> 00:17:32,267
and the ten million in cash.

290
00:17:32,400 --> 00:17:34,233
This is not possible!

291
00:17:34,367 --> 00:17:35,567
And I don't care

292
00:17:35,700 --> 00:17:38,167
if he bequeaths
even one property to her!

293
00:17:38,300 --> 00:17:40,433
Because in the first place,

294
00:17:40,567 --> 00:17:43,167
she shouldn't be bequeathed!

295
00:17:43,300 --> 00:17:45,267
I want that rest house!

296
00:17:45,400 --> 00:17:48,600
Mommy, you never liked
that place, remember?

297
00:17:48,767 --> 00:17:49,667
You and daddy even fought

298
00:17:49,800 --> 00:17:50,567
because you were so angry

299
00:17:50,700 --> 00:17:52,300
when he bought you
that rest house

300
00:17:52,433 --> 00:17:54,300
as a gift for your birthday,
remember?

301
00:17:54,433 --> 00:17:56,867
Exactly!

302
00:17:57,000 --> 00:18:00,333
It was a gift for me!

303
00:18:00,467 --> 00:18:04,200
So it doesn't matter
if I like it or not!

304
00:18:04,333 --> 00:18:06,467
Mom, please stop it.

305
00:18:06,600 --> 00:18:07,800
It's embarrassing
for the Attorney.

306
00:18:07,933 --> 00:18:09,300
It's embarrassing?

307
00:18:09,433 --> 00:18:10,533
Yes.

308
00:18:10,667 --> 00:18:12,900
Isn't it more embarrassing

309
00:18:13,033 --> 00:18:14,567
for this illegitimate child

310
00:18:14,700 --> 00:18:18,133
to be meddling
in the family inheritance?

311
00:18:20,833 --> 00:18:26,033
If you have any dignity
or decency left

312
00:18:26,200 --> 00:18:28,867
in the bones of your body,

313
00:18:29,000 --> 00:18:31,167
you will disclaim
your inheritance...

314
00:18:31,300 --> 00:18:35,033
Mom! Please stop it!

315
00:18:35,167 --> 00:18:36,967
This is dad's last will.

316
00:18:38,467 --> 00:18:41,267
Are we going to deny him that?

317
00:18:43,500 --> 00:18:44,933
Let's just give it to him.

318
00:18:45,067 --> 00:18:46,200
Let's give Bobby

319
00:18:46,333 --> 00:18:48,800
what dad wants to give him.

320
00:18:49,900 --> 00:18:51,767
Please...

321
00:18:51,900 --> 00:18:54,067
Let's do it for dad.

322
00:19:08,733 --> 00:19:12,100
A resort and ten million pesos?

323
00:19:13,833 --> 00:19:15,233
Yes,

324
00:19:15,367 --> 00:19:16,767
but she's thinking about

325
00:19:16,900 --> 00:19:18,800
what he's going to do
with that inheritance.

326
00:19:18,933 --> 00:19:21,733
Oh, Captain, well...

327
00:19:21,867 --> 00:19:23,200
let's go on vacation.

328
00:19:23,333 --> 00:19:24,900
I will wearing my two-piece!

329
00:19:25,033 --> 00:19:26,267
Me, my one-piece!

330
00:19:27,900 --> 00:19:28,800
That's a shame.

331
00:19:28,933 --> 00:19:30,300
Stop it!

332
00:19:30,433 --> 00:19:32,967
Let's just wait and see
what Bobby decides.

333
00:19:33,100 --> 00:19:34,067
Okay.

334
00:19:34,200 --> 00:19:36,167
If you really don't want to go
on vacation,

335
00:19:36,300 --> 00:19:39,600
why don't we just split
the ten million pesos?

336
00:19:39,733 --> 00:19:41,433
And let's get a facelift.

337
00:19:41,567 --> 00:19:42,400
I'll get something done...

338
00:19:42,533 --> 00:19:43,533
I'll get a nose job,

339
00:19:43,667 --> 00:19:45,033
and then my hips,
they're a bit big.

340
00:19:45,167 --> 00:19:46,500
- Perfect!
- So I need to reduce her.

341
00:19:46,633 --> 00:19:48,100
- Isn't it?
- Stop it.

342
00:19:48,233 --> 00:19:50,433
The ten million isn't enough
for your facelift.

343
00:19:50,567 --> 00:19:51,833
- Oh my...
- You're really bad, Captain.

344
00:19:51,967 --> 00:19:53,600
- You're insulting us.
- That's right.

345
00:19:53,733 --> 00:19:57,433
Hey, Captain, where's Bobby?

346
00:19:57,567 --> 00:19:58,400
She went home.

347
00:19:58,533 --> 00:20:01,133
She said he wanted to be alone.

348
00:20:01,300 --> 00:20:03,733
I'll go home first.

349
00:20:03,867 --> 00:20:06,767
I'll cook him a delicious meal.

350
00:20:06,900 --> 00:20:08,033
- You stay there.
- Captain,

351
00:20:08,167 --> 00:20:09,467
set aside some food for us.

352
00:20:10,500 --> 00:20:12,433
I hope Captain's cooking
is delicious.

353
00:20:14,033 --> 00:20:16,233
- It's Zondra!
- Oh, why?

354
00:20:16,367 --> 00:20:18,100
- She was killed!
- Killed?

355
00:20:18,233 --> 00:20:20,333
Yes, and they're asking
for donations.

356
00:20:20,467 --> 00:20:22,300
Oh no, I feel like
this is a hate crime.

357
00:20:22,433 --> 00:20:23,700
What makes you say that, Mar?

358
00:20:23,833 --> 00:20:25,867
They're killing
all the beautiful gays.

359
00:20:26,000 --> 00:20:27,067
Oh no, I got nervous.

360
00:20:27,200 --> 00:20:29,233
- What do I do?
- That's why.

361
00:20:29,367 --> 00:20:30,933
- Yes.
- Don't be nervous.

362
00:20:31,067 --> 00:20:32,400
Poor Zondra.

363
00:20:32,533 --> 00:20:34,000
That's why.

364
00:20:34,133 --> 00:20:35,633
There, oh.

365
00:20:37,700 --> 00:20:39,933
Zondra!

366
00:20:41,067 --> 00:20:42,433
Zondra!

367
00:20:42,567 --> 00:20:46,367
Zondra, don't leave me!

368
00:20:46,500 --> 00:20:47,767
Mother!

369
00:20:47,900 --> 00:20:50,133
She said she's the victim's
daughter.

370
00:20:50,267 --> 00:20:52,333
What's going on
in the world right now?

371
00:20:53,367 --> 00:20:55,633
But, Bok, I don't know
what it feels like

372
00:20:55,767 --> 00:20:58,200
to lose a loved one.

373
00:21:00,533 --> 00:21:03,300
Oh, when you're put
in that situation,

374
00:21:03,433 --> 00:21:06,367
you really don't know
what to do.

375
00:21:06,500 --> 00:21:08,333
It seems like nothing
can prepare you

376
00:21:08,500 --> 00:21:11,567
for the kind of pain
you're going to feel.

377
00:21:28,567 --> 00:21:29,900
We don't even have a picture

378
00:21:30,033 --> 00:21:31,500
of the two of us together,
Father.

379
00:21:35,167 --> 00:21:37,833
It took a while
before I accepted you.

380
00:21:39,600 --> 00:21:41,600
I was so fussy!

381
00:21:48,167 --> 00:21:49,600
Grandchild...

382
00:21:50,867 --> 00:21:53,967
I know you're sad.

383
00:21:54,100 --> 00:21:56,367
Bobby, we're just here...

384
00:21:57,667 --> 00:21:59,567
if you need someone to talk to.

385
00:22:00,733 --> 00:22:02,967
And don't forget

386
00:22:03,100 --> 00:22:05,800
we were close friends
before you got rich.

387
00:22:06,900 --> 00:22:08,367
That's right, Bobby.

388
00:22:08,500 --> 00:22:12,433
But if you don't want
the ten million,

389
00:22:12,567 --> 00:22:13,867
then you can give it
to Mar and me.

390
00:22:14,000 --> 00:22:15,167
We're okay with that...

391
00:22:16,767 --> 00:22:18,133
What's with you?

392
00:22:19,167 --> 00:22:21,400
What ten million
are you talking about?

393
00:22:22,900 --> 00:22:25,500
What are you thinking,
granddaughter?

394
00:22:25,633 --> 00:22:28,200
I'm just sorry, Grandmother.

395
00:22:28,333 --> 00:22:31,033
I only got to spend
a little time with father.

396
00:22:31,167 --> 00:22:33,733
I still have so much
to tell him.

397
00:22:34,767 --> 00:22:38,267
I hope he'll show himself to me,

398
00:22:38,400 --> 00:22:39,933
even if it's just in a dream.

399
00:22:40,067 --> 00:22:42,767
Oh, Bobby, we know someone,
a psychic.

400
00:22:42,900 --> 00:22:44,100
Right, Mar?

401
00:22:44,233 --> 00:22:46,000
Oh, yes!

402
00:22:46,133 --> 00:22:49,633
It's like the soul
of the departed enters her body,

403
00:22:49,800 --> 00:22:52,267
and then you can talk to him.

404
00:22:52,700 --> 00:22:53,933
Right?

405
00:22:55,167 --> 00:22:57,267
You two are something else,
what are you talking about?

406
00:22:57,400 --> 00:22:58,433
Psychic?

407
00:22:58,567 --> 00:22:59,800
That's a scam.

408
00:22:59,933 --> 00:23:02,233
Oh, Grandmother, that's true,
isn't it?

409
00:23:02,367 --> 00:23:06,467
Yes, the one we know,
she's good!

410
00:23:06,600 --> 00:23:08,633
It's Madam Alma.

411
00:23:10,233 --> 00:23:11,933
Are you ready, Mother?

412
00:23:13,300 --> 00:23:15,533
We need to take a deep breath.

413
00:23:19,267 --> 00:23:20,367
Another one.

414
00:23:25,400 --> 00:23:27,967
Hold my hands.

415
00:23:28,100 --> 00:23:30,833
Let's close our eyes
together, okay?

416
00:23:30,967 --> 00:23:32,933
One...

417
00:23:33,067 --> 00:23:35,133
Two...

418
00:23:35,267 --> 00:23:36,867
Three...

419
00:23:39,400 --> 00:23:41,733
Don't open your eyes.

420
00:24:10,767 --> 00:24:12,233
I was just asking her for help

421
00:24:12,500 --> 00:24:14,767
to find out
who killed my mother,

422
00:24:14,900 --> 00:24:17,467
And then I found out
she was just acting!

423
00:24:17,600 --> 00:24:18,733
Hey, what acting?

424
00:24:18,867 --> 00:24:19,967
What acting
are you talking about?

425
00:24:20,100 --> 00:24:21,833
Do you have proof?

426
00:24:25,367 --> 00:24:26,633
I saw something!

427
00:24:26,767 --> 00:24:27,433
Icepick!

428
00:24:27,567 --> 00:24:28,733
- Icepick?
- I saw it, yes!

429
00:24:28,900 --> 00:24:29,967
I can't believe it.

430
00:24:30,100 --> 00:24:32,900
The details she gave
are exactly the same.

431
00:24:33,033 --> 00:24:34,833
How would Alma know

432
00:24:34,967 --> 00:24:36,633
about Zondra's files?

433
00:24:36,767 --> 00:24:39,100
It's only been days
since nilibing si daddy.

434
00:24:39,233 --> 00:24:40,567
We have different means
of coping up.

435
00:24:40,700 --> 00:24:42,100
Yours is so different.

436
00:24:42,233 --> 00:24:43,267
Because out of the three of us,

437
00:24:43,400 --> 00:24:44,867
You seem to be the one
who is least affected

438
00:24:45,000 --> 00:24:46,300
by daddy's loss.

439
00:24:46,433 --> 00:24:48,567
You have a visitor.

440
00:24:48,700 --> 00:24:50,600
- Who?
- There, oh.

441
00:24:50,733 --> 00:24:52,767
- Bobby.
- Tonyo.
